Package com.doa.engine.input

Class DoaKeyboard

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.doa.engine.input.DoaKeyboard
  • public final class DoaKeyboard
extends java.lang.Object
    Responsible for catching all fired keyboard inputs at any logical frame. This class is static, therefore has no objects.
    Since:
    DoaEngine 1.0
    Version:
    1.1
    Author:

    • Field Detail

      • INPUT

        public static final java.awt.event.KeyAdapter INPUT
        This construct ensures all key events in any logical frame to be captured and saved in this class' internal state. At any logical frame, a reference to any of this class' fields will return true if and only if that reference mask has been produced according to a captured key event. Informally, if a key has been pressed at any time, at that time the respective field will be set to true, and when the same key has been released the same field will be set to false.
        See Also:
        KeyAdapter

    • Method Detail

      • tick

        public static void tick()
        This method is required to be public, but should never be called explicitly by any class at any time except DoaEngine. If done otherwise, DoaEngine provides no guarantees on the consistency of the KeyEvent catching mechanism.
